<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1895-11-24T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1895-11-24T00:00:00-05:00" n="642" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d642">
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Terrell</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Olney</persName>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Pera</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1895-11-24"><hi rend="italic">November 24,
                                    1895</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>Telegrams from Aintab and Marsovan report missionaries safe and
                            protected. Am now able to report that all our 172 missionaries in Turkey
                            are protected. Porte gives assurances tranquillity will soon be
                            restored. I request that ships remain in the Mediterranean, and that
                            commanders keep me advised of their anchorage.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Terrell.</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>